First Insights Invoice Finance User¶

This notebook has been generated on 24/04/2020

The objective of this notebook is to analyse why companies use invoice finance service. We focus on the data where company use invoice finance service. We try to find what kind of company and the size of company use this service more.

Analysis steps¶

The analysis steps performed in this notebook are the following

  • Company starts to use invoice financial service

  • Mapping Invoice Finance User

    • Overview Dataset
    • Categorical analysis
    • Continuous analysis

Data source¶

The data source of this dataset is:

- table: `ci01_user_not_user_ac01ac06_final`
- table:`companies_invoice`

2.5 company_accounts information¶

the top 3 company type are related to small company type information

Definition

  • Total Exemption Full - this term refers to medium or small business' filing full accounts.
  • A micro-entity is a very small company or LLP. Micro-entities may be able to produce a much simpler set of year end accounts for their members and provide less information for the public record
  • Total Exemption Small - this term refers to medium or small companies that file only the abbreviated accounts at companies house.

Insight

According to our understanding, the top 3 company type are related to small company type information. Total Exemption full 44.71, micro-entity accounts 17.85, total exemption small 12.7, so, in total, we have 75.26% companies accounts related to small company type

Continuous variables analysis¶

For deeper understanding of the variables, please refer to this document made by Credit Safe

  • 3.1 currat: Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities
  • 3.2 gear: Bank Overdraft and Loans plus Total Long Term Liabilities/Shareholders funds x 100
  • 3.3 equi: Shareholder Funds / (Total Current Assets + Tangible Fixed Assets) x 100
  • 3.4 liqtest: Current assets - Stocks/Current Liabilities
  • 3.5 cudbr: Total Current Liabilities / Shareholders Funds
  • 3.6 totdbr: Total Short Term & Long Term Debt / Shareholder Funds

3.1 currat¶

Half of service users has more current liabilities than current assets

Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities. This is an indication of a company's ability to meet short-term debt obligations, the higher the ratio, the more liquid the company is.

From the result below, there are 13301 company has this variable information. We can find 50% companies are lower than 1. It means, around half of service users has more current liabilities than current assets. The liquidation situation is not very well.
